c is the degree of polymerization, 1≤c≤250;
d is the degree of polymerization, 1≤d≤166;
e is the degree of polymerization, 1≤e≤125;
R is a terminal group having any of the structures of Formula (Va), Formula (Vb), Formula (Vc), Formula (Vd), and Formula (Ve).

Preferably, the solvent is water, physiological saline, or buffer solution;
the polyethylene glycol derivative has a mass-volume concentration of 1˜1000 mg/mL; and
the polyethylene glycol having an amino-containing terminal group has a mass-volume concentration of 1˜1000 mg/mL.

